      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.themes.Item.cmnIJbltlo1d5oZn]{Prisoner}</p>\n<p>While imprisoned, you had limited resources to defend yourself with, and often had to make do with what you had at hand at the time. When using a nonweapon object as an @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.JournalEntry.Nrf6oy9pJwcEmryP.JournalEntryPage.21wLdW9boKwLHuxn]{improvised weapon} (Core Rulebook 169), you don’t treat it as @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.JournalEntry.Nrf6oy9pJwcEmryP.JournalEntryPage.nXkFsyxk7Vybdn7G#archaic]{archaic}, and if you would take a –4 penalty to attacks with that weapon because it is improvised, that penalty is reduced by 2.</p>"
